monitorThread.setDaemon(true);
monitorThread.setName("log-monitor-thread");
monitorThread.start();
```
- **`setDaemon(true)`** — Marks this as a background (daemon) thread. When the main app shuts down, the JVM won't wait for daemon threads to finish — it just kills them. Perfect for a watcher that has no critical work to complete.
- **`setName(...)`** — Names the thread for easier debugging in thread dumps/profilers.
- **`start()`** — *Now* the thread actually begins executing. Everything before this was just setup.

